---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 2
title: Industries
description: Sovereign AI use cases for Switzerland's regulated sectors — banking & finance, healthcare & pharma, legal, government, insurance and manufacturing. Custom models fine-tuned on Apertus, deployed on-prem with zero data egress.
faq:
  - q: Which industries do you serve?
    a: We focus on regulated and data-sensitive sectors in Switzerland and the EU — banking and finance, healthcare and pharma, legal and professional services, government and the public sector, insurance, and manufacturing. These are the organisations for whom sovereignty, privacy and compliance are non-negotiable.
  - q: Can you work with our existing systems?
    a: Yes. Agents built with LangGraph call into your existing systems and data sources through tools and RAG, so the AI works with your core banking, EHR, DMS, ERP or case-management systems rather than replacing them.
  - q: We operate across languages — is that supported?
    a: Apertus is multilingual across 1,000+ languages, including Swiss German, French, Italian and Romansh. That makes it well suited to Swiss and EU organisations operating across national languages.
---
{% from "partials/components.njk" import sectionHead, cta %}

<section class="border-b border-ink-900/10 dark:border-white/10">
  <div class="container-x py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">Industries</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      Built for the sectors that can't send data away.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
      Where confidentiality, sovereignty and compliance are non-negotiable, sysf.io turns AI from a blocked pilot into a production system you own.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

